modules.description: This module supports evaluating string inputs and managing output printers. It works with string lists and boolean outcomes, providing direct control over printer installation and string evaluation. Use cases include scripting interfaces and dynamic configuration parsing.

This module provides functions to convert MAC addresses between string, octet, and internal representations, supporting parsing, formatting, and validation. It works with MAC addresses as 6-byte strings and a structured type `t` representing individual addresses. Concrete use cases include parsing MAC addresses from configuration files, generating locally administered addresses, and validating MAC strings in network management tools.
